						               													<description>Le diable du pont de Valentr&amp;eacute; (literally &amp;quot;The devil from Valentr&amp;eacute;'s bridge&amp;quot;) is a card game for 2 to 6 players inspired by a French tale and a comic book drawn by the game author. Each player plays the architect in charge of building Valentr&amp;eacute;'s bridge, but as the legend says, the devil comes at night to steal stones from the bridge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is a classic card game where at his turn, each player draws a card and then can either get the resources necessary to build the bridge (so-called &amp;quot;key&amp;quot; cards), protect his keys (&amp;quot;shield&amp;quot; cards), attack  an opponent (&amp;quot;claws&amp;quot; cards), build his bridge or discard.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after the first player builds the bridge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
